<h2> Duct Tape Wallet </h2>

My leather wallet recently started falling apart.  I like the aesthetics of duct tape wallets and was thinking about buying one, but in decided to make one of my own with some unique features.  <a href="http://www.instructables.com/id/quality-duct-tape-wallet/" > Here</a> is a how-to guide that I consulted for some of the basic techniques. </br> </br>

I was pleased with the final product: </br> </br>
<img src="wallet1.jpg" width="400" </a></br></br>
I put a few decals on the exterior to improve the look. </br> </br>

<img src="wallet2.jpg" width="400" </a></br></br>
The wallet looks like this when opened.  I added two card pockets, one at a right angle from the other to help differentiate them.  There's also a clear middle pouch that works well for pictures.</br> </br>

<img src="wallet3.jpg" width="400" </a></br>
The cash pouch. </br> </br>

<img src="wallet4.jpg" width="400" </a></br>
The side pouch opens up and allows me to store some other small items, like change.  I added snap fasteners from an old pair of cargo shorts. </br> </br>

<img src="wallet5.jpg" width="400" </a></br>
The brown rubber cap on the side pouch pulls off to reveal a 1GB USB flash drive. </br> </br>

<img src="wallet6.jpg" width="400" </a></br>
The USB drive in action.

